section.section:
An instrument must be executed by any two of:
the State Treasurer;
the Executive Director of the State Retirement Agency;
the Chief Investment Officer of the State Retirement Agency; or
another employee of the State Retirement Agency as the Executive Director designates with the approval of the Board of Trustees.

The Board of Trustees shall keep records required by paragraph (1) of this subsection for each of the following:
the group that consists of the Correctional Officers' Retirement System, the Employees' Pension System, the Employees' Retirement System, and the Legislative Pension Plan;
the Judges' Retirement System;
the Local Fire and Police System;
the Law Enforcement Officers' Pension System;
the State Police Retirement System;
the group that consists of the Teachers' Pension System and the Teachers' Retirement System; and
the Postretirement Health Benefits Trust Fund.
